  "text": "Lee et al. found that serum IGF-1 levels were lower in NSCLC patients than in the SCLC group. They reported that serum levels of IGF-1 and IGFBPs might be useful markers for diagnosing and identifying tumor types in lung cancer. [CITATION_1] In contrast to this finding, we did not find any significant relationship between IGF-1, IGFBP-3 levels and histopathologic type both in serum and ELF. Also there was no relation between the tumor localization, diameter and IGF-1, IGFBP-3 levels in serum and ELF.",
